---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Markdown from '../components/Markdown.astro';
import '../../src/styles/word-count.css';

const explainer = `
# H1 - Fonts: Cal Sans
## H2 - DM Sans
### H3 - Didact Gothic

Most of the CSS should be complete. Reorganize it and then add some more text styling  too if needed.
MAKE THE UTILITIES NOW!

# Old Text

An Astro website can go way beyond static pages - on the right platform.

Netlify supports not only [Streaming SSR](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/server-side-rendering/#html-streaming) and fast [Edge Middleware](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/middleware/), but also [on-demand revalidation](https://www.netlify.com/blog/cache-tags-and-purge-api-on-netlify/) and [stale-while-revalidate](https://www.netlify.com/blog/swr-and-fine-grained-cache-control/).
Any page or data can be rebuilt only when needed, without site visitors ever getting a performance hit.
`;
---


<Layout title="Welcome to Astro.">
    <h1>Word Counter</h1>

    <!-- Textbox -->
    <div class="word-container"> <!-- Everything placed here -->

                <div class="output-container"> <!-- Where the info is placed. -->
                    <div class="output"> <!-- Fancy edition. -->
                        <p class="words">Words</p>
                        <span data-word-count>0</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="output">
                        <p class="characters">Characters</p>
                        <span data-character-count>0</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="output">
                        <p class="sentences">Sentences</p>
                        <span data-sentence-count>0</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="output">
                        <p class="paragraphs">Paragraphs</p>
                        <span data-paragraph-count>0</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                    <textarea placeholder="Enter your text here..."></textarea>
    </div>

    <script src="src/pages/functions/counter.js" defer></script>

</Layout>


